cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with text classification using deep neural networks and statistical hypothesis testing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of statistical hypothesis testing for feature selection and classification makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of label descriptions, which is a common technique in natural language processing, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves image classification, which could make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
